originalText.text:
I had a super good experience with one provider that I stuck with. She left the practice. I've tried 3 different therapists from here since. I had the first one say, "You have a lot of trauma," no duh. The second one, I just felt was a bad match.
The third one that had me packing diagnosed me with OCD. She did not know what she was doing in my opinion. She said things like, "I wonder if that is a compulsion once I said anything..." or, "What if you just stopped doing the compulsions? What would that look like?" I sat there like um, I am here because I can't stop. My OCD compulsions are not gonna stop overnight? I don't understand why she felt like I could just stop. She realized that I wasn't gonna just stop because she never gave me any resources for coping and by the third session was like, "I don't think I can help you, maybe, you'd be better off with someone else," yet she proceeded with the session???? During the same session, she stated I was dishonest and lying to her about my body image issues as I had said I felt okay with the way I looked in the first session. I wanted to build trust with her. I eventually got to talking about the way I really felt. She then said, "Why lie? Do you lie to your doctor?" I then held it together to the end of the session and proceeded to cry after the session.

originalText.text: Warning: Received first bill for my husband's therapy today. $529 per hour!!! What on earth?!!
